docs.abstract: A factory whose survival was a central issue in last year’s 40-day strike will get a $2.2 billion infusion for next-generation vehicles.
docs.snippet: A factory whose survival was a central issue in last year’s 40-day strike will get a $2.2 billion infusion for next-generation vehicles.
docs.lead_paragraph: General Motors said Monday that it was investing $2.2 billion in a Detroit plant where it will produce all-electric trucks and sport utility vehicles, fulfilling a key promise made during last year’s union negotiations.

headline.main: G.M. Making Detroit Plant a Hub of Electric and A.V. Efforts
headline.print_headline: G.M. to Pour Billions  Into Hub for Electric And Self-Driving Cars

docs.abstract: The spread of the dangerous virus has spooked global markets and threatened prospects for economic growth.
docs.snippet: The spread of the dangerous virus has spooked global markets and threatened prospects for economic growth.
docs.lead_paragraph: Before a mysterious respiratory illness emerged in the center of China, spreading with lethal effect through the world’s most populous nation, concerns about the health of the global economy had been easing, replaced by a measure of optimism.

headline.main: China’s Coronavirus Has Revived Global Economic Fears
headline.print_headline: Worry Over Chinese Outbreak Spreads Into Global Markets

docs.abstract: Jim Rich, who presided over a Pulitzer, will take over at a freewheeling sports site that has posted almost nothing since its staff quit last fall.
docs.snippet: Jim Rich, who presided over a Pulitzer, will take over at a freewheeling sports site that has posted almost nothing since its staff quit last fall.
docs.lead_paragraph: The publisher of the irreverent sports website Deadspin tapped a former editor in chief of The Daily News on Thursday to lead rebuilding efforts, nearly three months after a staff exodus over what employees characterized as editorial meddling.

headline.main: Editor Who Sharpened Daily News Is Picked to Revive Deadspin
headline.print_headline: Ex-Editor of Daily News To Resuscitate Deadspin

docs.abstract: As hedge funds take a greater role in newspaper chains, journalists at the Chicago Tribune and elsewhere are sending out an S.O.S.
docs.snippet: As hedge funds take a greater role in newspaper chains, journalists at the Chicago Tribune and elsewhere are sending out an S.O.S.
docs.lead_paragraph: On a cold Chicago morning last month, Gary Marx, a veteran investigative reporter, took his dog for a walk and then strolled over to the affluent Lincoln Park neighborhood. After being buzzed into the courtyard of a large house, he hand-delivered a letter urging the intended recipient to buy — or at least invest in — Mr. Marx’s journalistic home of more than three decades, The Chicago Tribune.

headline.main: Worried Reporters Make a Plea: Please Buy Our Paper
headline.print_headline: Reporters Make a Plea: Please Buy Our Paper

docs.abstract: The sheer volume of criticism of the government, and the sometimes clever ways that critics dodge censors, are testing Beijing’s ability to control the narrative.
docs.snippet: The sheer volume of criticism of the government, and the sometimes clever ways that critics dodge censors, are testing Beijing’s ability to control the narrative.
docs.lead_paragraph: SHANGHAI — Recently, someone following the coronavirus crisis through China’s official news media would see lots of footage, often set to stirring music, praising the heroism and sacrifice of health workers marching off to stricken places.

headline.main: As Virus Spreads, Anger Floods Chinese Social Media
headline.print_headline: On Chinese Social Media, Anger Over Virus

docs.abstract: The internet giant posted increases in revenue and profit after shoppers flocked to it during the holiday season.
docs.snippet: The internet giant posted increases in revenue and profit after shoppers flocked to it during the holiday season.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Amazon sold a lot of things to a lot of people in the last three months of 2019, as speedy shipping shortened the time between “I want it” and “It’s here.”

headline.main: Amazon Powers Ahead With Robust Profit
headline.print_headline: Amazon Powers Forward With Hefty Quarterly Profit

docs.abstract: The classic auto market, humming just a few years ago, appears to be sliding into a downturn.
docs.snippet: The classic auto market, humming just a few years ago, appears to be sliding into a downturn.
docs.lead_paragraph: SCOTTSDALE, Ariz. — When classic cars hit the auction block these days, $3 million seems to be the new $10 million.

headline.main: Where Did the $9 Million Cars Go?
headline.print_headline: Price Drop Gives Classics That Old Car Smell

docs.abstract: It said the decision was based on the efforts by the industry to prevent meaningful climate action by governments.
docs.snippet: It said the decision was based on the efforts by the industry to prevent meaningful climate action by governments.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — The Guardian newspaper said it would stop accepting advertisements from oil and gas companies, making it the latest institution to limit financial ties to fossil fuel businesses.

headline.main: ‘Every Day Matters’: Guardian Stops Accepting Fossil Fuel Ads
headline.print_headline: British Newspaper Stops Taking Ads From Oil and Gas Companies

docs.abstract: American, Delta and United will halt service to the Chinese mainland, widening the impact of the outbreak on business and travel.
docs.snippet: American, Delta and United will halt service to the Chinese mainland, widening the impact of the outbreak on business and travel.
docs.lead_paragraph: Delta Air Lines, American Airlines and United Airlines said on Friday morning that they were suspending service between the United States and China — drastically limiting service just hours before the Trump administration issued new travel restrictions of its own.

headline.main: 3 Major U.S. Airlines Suspend China Flights Over Coronavirus

docs.abstract: The city, stepping into a debate over privacy, says it will use real-time facial recognition technology “to tackle serious crime.”
docs.snippet: The city, stepping into a debate over privacy, says it will use real-time facial recognition technology “to tackle serious crime.”
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — London’s police department said on Friday that it would begin using facial recognition to spot criminal suspects with video cameras as they walk the streets, adopting a level of surveillance that is rare outside China.

headline.main: London Police Are Taking Surveillance to a Whole New Level
headline.print_headline: London Police  Will Start Using Facial ID Tools
